SDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of premium and interest rate components. The funding fee is exchanged between long and short position holders when the perpetual trades at a premium or discount to the index price. OKX's portfolio margin mode allows efficient capital utilization when running multiple funding arbitrage positions simultaneously."}]]}],"$L3",["$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}],"$L8"]}]]}],["$L9","$La"],"$Lb"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TRX","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TRX exhibits consistent funding rate patterns due to its large retail following and strong correlation with broader crypto sentiment. The pair's high liquidity on OKX ensures minimal slippage when entering arbitrage positions, while TRON's relatively low volatility reduces directional risk during rate collection periods."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TRX/USDT funding rates on OKX typically range from -0.1% to 0.3% during normal market conditions, with spikes above 0.5% during strong rallies. The pair shows pronounced weekend effects where rates often turn negative due to reduced retail activity. Quarterly patterns emerge around TRON ecosystem updates and Justin Sun announcements, creating predictable rate volatility windows. Historical data shows TRX funding rates lag Bitcoin by 2-4 hours, providing early signals for rate direction changes."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage works best when OKX TRX rates diverge from Binance or Bybit by more than 0.05% per 8-hour cycle. Calendar spread arbitrage using TRX quarterly futures against perpetuals can capture term structure inefficiencies during high volatility periods. Delta-neutral strategies combining TRX perpetuals with spot holdings benefit from OKX's integrated wallet system for seamless transfers. Multi-leg arbitrage involving TRX, BTT, and JST perpetuals exploits TRON ecosystem correlation breakdowns."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TRX's sensitivity to regulatory news about TRON Foundation creates sudden funding rate spikes that can turn profitable positions negative within hours. Auto-deleveraging risk increases during Justin Sun's social media activity periods when TRX volatility surges unexpectedly. OKX's insurance fund coverage for TRX is lower than major pairs, increasing counterparty risk during extreme market stress. Funding rate caps at ±0.75% per cycle can limit arbitrage profits during optimal conditions but provide downside protection."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does OKX update TRX/USDT funding rates?","answer":"OKX updates TRX/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The rate is calculated using a time-weighted average during the final hour before each funding timestamp."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for TRX funding arbitrage on OKX?","answer":"The minimum order size is 1 TRX, but profitable funding arbitrage typically requires positions of at least 10,000 TRX to overcome trading fees. OKX's 0.02% maker fees mean you need funding rates above 0.06% per cycle to break even on round-trip trades."},{"question":"Can I use portfolio margin for TRX funding strategies?","answer":"Yes, OKX's portfolio margin mode allows cross-margining TRX positions with other assets, reducing capital requirements. This is particularly effective for multi-pair funding strategies involving TRON ecosystem tokens like BTT and JST."},{"question":"How does TRX funding compare to other L1 tokens on OKX?","answer":"TRX typically has more stable funding rates than Ethereum or Solana due to lower volatility and different user demographics. Rates are generally positive but less extreme than newer L1s, making it suitable for consistent yield strategies rather than high-risk arbitrage plays."}]}]
